                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto)" facs="001 002"/>
                      Crude drawings and isolated text in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    <locus target="#126v" facs="129"/>
                     Note of ownership by Wäldä Ḥawaryat, son of Täklä Haymanot
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#126v" facs="129"> f. 126v, in blue ink at the bottom</locus>
                    A list of baptismal names, Gäbrä Yoḥannǝs and Mahdärä Maryam
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    Binding is original and intact and is in very good condition
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    Vellum is in very good condition with only a little discoloration
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#1 #6 #13 #19 #28 #34 #39 #47 #56 #62 #66 #76 #87 #89 #95 #101 #111 #117" facs="003 008 015 021 030 036 041 049 058 064 068 078 089 097 103 113 119"/>
                      Navigation systems:
                      yellow thread is sewn into the fore edge to mark content
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                      Scribal intervention:
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#17v" facs="020"/>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#74v" facs="077"/>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#65r #93v #99r" facs="067 096 101"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#5v #6r #7r" facs="008 009"/>). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#7v #8r #9r" facs="010 011"/>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
